&lt;p&gt;Unscheduled Care is an exciting, diverse and large acute division which encompass many specialities – every day is different!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although a large division within the Trust we still retain a close knit family feel. We will ensure that your skills are utilised in the best possible way and our Senior Nursing Team are committed to ensuring our staff feel supported in their roles, which reflects on patients and their families receiving the best care possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for highly motivated and committed Band 5 Staff Nurses to work across the Specialities of Medicine. There are a variety of posts available including the Acute Medical Unit, Ambulatory Emergency Care Unit, Wards 2, 6, 24 &amp; C General Medical, Ward 3 Oncology, Wards 5, 7, 10 Respiratory ,Ward 11 Endocrinology, Ward 12 Gastroenterology, Wards 23, 25, 26 Acute Care of the Older Person, Haematology Ward, Ward 8 Isolation Unit and our Stroke Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All nurses new to our Division receive protected supernumerary time and training and development opportunities with our dedicated bespoke Practice Development Team. Newly Qualified and Return to Practice Nurses will also receive protected Preceptorship time for 12 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;These positions are available to Student Nurses, we would also welcome applicants who are interested in a Secondment Opportunity.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible Working Patterns may also be available upon discussion, such as Night Shifts or Part-time hours, please discuss at Interview stage.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
